				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Your simplification doesn't look correct.
<br />
<br />You need the following state, with indicated number of bits:
<br />
<br />1 Flag
<br />8 Shadow
<br />7 Linear counter
<br />
<br />And the following behaviors:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">$4008 write:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; Shadow = value written<br /><br />$400B write:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; Flag = 1<br /><br />Linear clock:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; If Flag = 1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Linear counter = low 7 bits of Shadow<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; else if Linear counter &gt; 0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Linear counter = Linear counter - 1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; If bit 7 of Shadow = 0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Flag = 0<br /><br />Frequency timer output clock:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; If length counter and linear counter are both non-zero<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; go to next step in triangle wave</div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
